body.description: With the BOB revolution flex 3.0, you can say yes to any type of family outing-whether prepping for a 10K or heading out for a day at the zoo. The suspension system keeps you running smoothly and the adjustable handlebar fits parents of all heights. The seat is designed with compression padding for all-day comfort and sits fully-upright so your little rider can take in the world. The extra-large UPF 50+ canopy shields from the sun and includes a magnetic "peek & chat" Window so you can check on and chat with your child along the way. With a spacious cargo basket and six storage pockets, you'll have plenty of room for all your gear and can keep your cell phone close-at-hand. The swivel-locking front wheel maneuvers easily through crowded streets and locks for stability when jogging while the reflective accents keep you safe on all your journeys (lunar black fashion is ultra-reflective). Adventures are boundless with the BOB revolution flex 3.0 jogging stroller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best heavy duty stroller on the market
reviews.reviewText: This is by far my favorite stroller. Please note it is a little heavy but you definitely get used to it. It is high-quality, heavy duty, smooth ride and does great on pebbles and grass as well. My kids love that they can sit together. Totally worth the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Expensive but worth EVERY penny!!
reviews.reviewText: We had a Bob single stroller that we used with our first child until she was 7 for big trips and vacations. It was the absolute best thing ever! When we had two more littles though we couldn't bring ourselves to spend this kind of money for the dual stroller. We bought several other tandum styles that we ended up returning for various reasons. None of them handled well with two kids, and most were bulky and awkward! We finally bought this one and are sooooo glad we did!! It handles like a dream and can turn on a dime! It's pretty narrow for a side by side and I found myself making it through openings I didn't think we would. The wheels are an absolute dream and can make it over ANY terrain and with ease! The seats are roomy and comfy. The underneath storage is fabulous. The height of the handles is perfect and ergonomic. The kids are up high and can see everything around them!! I mean I could go on and on!! Just buy it already!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the investment!
reviews.reviewText: I love how versatile and user friendly this stroller is! It’s absolutely worth the price tag. They last forever, it’s super easy to push and maneuver, folds up really nicely, and has really user friendly attachments. It is pricy but I would recommend it again and again. If you’re looking for a sign to purchase it, let this be the review you need!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this!
reviews.reviewText: This stroller is BIG. it’s sturdy. Moves well. For the price I am very happy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely worth it. Wish we could have caved and bought it as soon as we knew we were having two. Weight is a bit heavy, but worth it because the ride is so smooth and easy to navigate. We’ve used it at Disney, zoos, parks, and countless other places. Difficult to get through some doors, but usually can find another entrance/exit to utilize. We bought the attachments with cup holders for us and the kids and it makes it so much better. Note: Buy extra tubes and hand pumps if you’re on the trails!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for trail jogging with my toddler and infant
reviews.reviewText: A bit pricey, but so are all double jogging strollers, from what I can tell. I love the sturdiness of the BOB. Folding it takes some practice, but it's not too difficult. It is a bit ungainly to put in my car, but again - which dualie jogging stroller isn't? I wish it had a brake, like my single BOB, for when I'm going down steep hills. Otherwise: love the amount of storage, my son's fit well in it, the shock absorption is EXCELLENT, and I'm grateful to have such a solid stroller for jogging on the trails.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Stroller with some small hiccups
reviews.reviewText: We live on a farm. We’ve got a half paved driveway with mostly gravel. Rough gravel. Around almost the whole property. Then it’s all mowed woody areas with creek beds and wildlife and dirt and mud and you name it. And this stroller rides over it all like a champ. The kids LOVE riding in it, they have taken many a naps at the zoo and I think Costco in it. It fits in those larger stores like Walmart but it doesn’t in places like tjmax unless you want some awkward backing up situations with many glares thrown your way. It runs amazing, walks amazing, totes around lunches and water bottles, it can withstand mud and rain and it definitely makes this momma and these kiddos happy. I love the ability to really vent the seat when they lay down, the magnetic flaps on top are awesome, and the hand break is great! Just maybe not in a hurry, it’s definitely a stop and think about it rather than a normal switch foot break. Definitely get the cup holder package, I didn’t and have been tortured by trying to find a cheap one to fit on it, and that has been awful. Also, you can fit a lot of junk in the trunk but the junk has to be skinny enough to wiggle in there first, definitely not easy. Overall great ride.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Expensive but worth it
reviews.reviewText: Ok this is seriously expensive for a jogger however it is worth every penny. It is effortless in pushing as it has bike quality bearings and tires. I really enjoy running and walking the twins now with effortless 10 mile outings. I have not had any issues with the tires as some have stated. The suspension is actually good and absorbs the bumps and uneven surfaces, glad to see this is not just a gimmick. The kids really enjoy it and are comfortable cruising along. The seatbelts are easy to operate unlike some others, we have gone through 4 strollers prior. Only down side is it is a little wide but that is expected with twin stroller. It is not intended to be a take to the store type of stroller, but for walks and runs this stroller is A+++

I bought this jogging stroller for taking my grandbabies out for a walk in the forested trails on our property. The toughness of the terrain was untenable with a regular stroller, so I searched recommended strollers and looked into ppls reviews. My first trip out, what a difference the stroller made. Unbelievable, crazy good! Happy grandma!

Es práctica, solo que muy pesada para mí . Muy fácil de instalar las piezascomo el barandal de frente de los niños . Aparte súper segura , se mueve muy fácilmente hasta con una mano. Ocupa casi toda la cajuela pero vale la pena

I got it because my child is tipping past 25kg. So far it can carry the weight of my child, diaper bags and other miscellanous stuff and still glide smoothly! In fact the stroller rolls so smoothly that even my wife can push it with all the added items. It can fit easily into trains, buses and can easily be folded into a car boot (takes some practice). Overall seriously good value for money!
It is very big but this is an amazing stroller, easy to drive and park. Comfortable and secure for baby.
Easy to assemble, excellent quality, fabulous suspension. Very easy to maneuver.
